The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Altman dead

 Robert: Caustic satirist

 Los Angeles, Nov. 21 

 (AP): Robert Altman, the caustic and irreverent satirist 

 behind M-A-S-H, Nashville and The Player 

 who made a career out of bucking Hollywood management and 

 story conventions, died at a Los Angeles hospital, his Sandcastle 

 5 Productions Company said today. He was 81.

 A five-time Academy Award nominee for best director he finally won a lifetime achievement Oscar in 2006.

 No other filmmaker has gotten a better shake than I have,Altman said while accepting the award. Im very fortunate in my career. Ive never had to direct a film I didnt choose or develop. 




